text: Edam is a city in the province of North Holland in the Netherlands. About 7,380 people live there. The town is part of the municipality of Edam- Volendam. It is famous for Edam cheese which was first made in the town. The town has a little pub and a young population. ==Other websites== Category:20th-century disestablishments in the Netherlands Category:Cities in North Holland Category:Former municipalities of North Holland Category:Edam- Volendam
title: Edam, Netherlands
